Package: toaster
Type: Package
Title: Big Data in-Database Analytics with Teradata Aster
Version: 0.3.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Kanevsky", "Gregory", , "gregory.kanevsky@teradata.com", c("aut","cre")),
    person("Switanek", "Nick", , "nicholas.switanek@teradata.com", "aut")
    )
Description: A consistent set of tools to perform in-database analytics 
    on Teradata Aster Big Data Discovery Platform. toaster (a.k.a 'to Aster') 
    embraces simple approach by performing tasks in 2 steps:
    compute in Aster - visualize and analyze in R. Its `compute` functions
    use distributed, highly scalable, and parallel SQL and map-reduce SQL/MR 
    functions on large data sets stored in Aster database. Then
    `create` functions visualize results with boxplots, scatterplots,
    histograms, heatmaps, word clouds, maps, or slope graphs. Advanced options
    such as faceting, coloring, labeling, and others are supported
    with most plots.
SystemRequirements: Teradata Aster Database 5.10 (AD5.10) or higher, 
    Teradata Aster Analytical Foundation 5.10 (AA5.10) or higher 
    (5.11 or higher is recommended)
Depends:
